        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 4:49AM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 449 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers along a line
extending from 6 miles northeast of Clio to Flushing to Gaines to 6
miles north of Gregory. Movement was northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Mount Morris, Linden, Howell, Clio, Byron, Gaines, Flint, Oak
Grove, Swartz Creek, and Beecher around 455 AM EDT.
Otter Lake, Burton, Lake Fenton, and Otisville around 500 AM EDT.
Grand Blanc and Fenton around 505 AM EDT.
Davison and Holly around 510 AM EDT.
Goodrich and Columbiaville around 515 AM EDT.
Hadley, Lapeer, Ortonville, and Clifford around 525 AM EDT.
North Branch around 530 AM EDT.
Metamora around 535 AM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include Franklin, Keego
Harbor, Goodland Township, Waterford, Plainfield, Rankin, Holly State
Recreation Area, Commerce, Silverwood, and Conway Township.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
